id: hac-suj3
title: Add typed automation validation and release-safe version contracts
description: Expose the official Home Assistant WebSocket automation validation contract through a typed agent-friendly command and repair scheduled releases so candidate version bumps cannot invalidate the test suite.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[7]: agents,api,automation,github-actions,home-assistant,release,websocket
created_at: "2026-07-23T04:54:32.200Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:29:22.693Z"
deadline: "2026-07-24T04:54:32.200Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T05:29:21.829Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "hassio ws validate-config accepts trigger, condition, and action JSON plus a combined file and maps them to the server-supported plural payload contract; empty and malformed validation input fails before network I/O with actionable errors; scheduled release candidate version mutation passes the complete release test suite without weakening package/src version parity; all help, output formats, docs, live redacted checks, 100/100/100/100 coverage, docstrings, file-size, security, pm, and release gates pass"
definition_of_ready: "Official docs, current Core source, live instance behavior, repository code, full pm lineage, and failed hosted run are understood"
goal: Complete stable Home Assistant API coverage for agent workflows
objective: Typed automation validation and release-safe candidate verification
value: Agents can validate automations without executing them while daily releases remain dependable
impact: Prevents unsafe trial-and-error automation writes and blocked scheduled releases
outcome: A fully documented typed validation command and green scheduled release rehearsal
why_now: Official/live contract research exposed the gap while GitHub issue #65 proves the current release regression
parent: hac-4s9j
reviewer: unbraind
risk: medium
confidence: 95
sprint: api-contracts-2026-07-23
release: 2026.7.23
resolution: Agents can validate trigger condition and action definitions without execution; scheduled release verification no longer depends on a stale version literal.
expected_result: Safe typed validation plus reliable daily release preparation.
actual_result: Live Home Assistant 2026.4.4 validation passed; PR #66 merged; hosted dry-run target v2026.7.23 passed without publication.
